> These links make the perfect hearty side for your Mother's Day brunch. Simply sear until
> golden and snappy on the outside and juicy on the inside, or remove the casings first and
> cook into a crumble—whatever your heart desires. Pro tip: Dip the sausages into syrup
> for a sweet and savory sensation that might just blow your mind.

== Stovetop Method ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #pan over medium-high heat.

Add @Maple Pork Breakfast Sausage{10%oz} and cook, turning occasionally, until browned
all over and cooked through, ~{8-12%minutes}.

== Oven Method ==

Preheat #oven to 425 degrees.

Place @Maple Pork Breakfast Sausage{10%oz} on a #baking sheet. Roast until browned and
cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}.